          question: `You are submitting a CFP (call for papers) to DEF CON. Your choice is between: (A) a highly technical talk on a new zero-knowledge proof tracing technique, or (B) a practical case study of how you traced a $200M Lazarus hack step-by-step with live code. Which is more likely to be accepted and why?`,
